        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0092.jpg" n="part1_p092.jpg" xml:id="img_0092" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part1_p092.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_92_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>[89]
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>So you see how such a consideration brings the technical realm immediately
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>into the relationship to problems of<ultimate_concern> ultimate concern</ultimate_concern>.
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>I had, two weeks ago, a meeting with some architects about church
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>building, and I had to give the introductory speech, and my main emphasis was honesty,
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>the principle of honesty. This was accepted by all of them. The question, of course, was:
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>what is, in a special religious group, the honest expression of what it means? Now if you
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>are ever in the occasion to build a house or to choose to rent a house, then think of
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>this principle before any other principle. And if you buy furniture for your house,
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_10" n="N010"/>think of this principle. Only if it is an HONEST EXPRESSION, of what you are, then
               <lb facs="#facs_92_tr_3_tl_11" n="N011"/>it will express your being and give happiness to you.
            </p>
            
        </div>
